8.10.22  10:37 am   did you figure out that the random number generator isn't random?

     sure. i'd suspect that's true. most of the simple ones are probably just seeded by the exact time of request

      i figured out that much but haven't figured out exactly how it works yet. curious to know if you've been able to prove this already or if you've figured out exactly how it works... will generate based on 1000.000.000 and get patterns, and 3 with 5s and 8s means yes and i can ask questions and get information but i need to know what the information is based on

     in this case, it's based on your imagination. most 9 digit numbers have patterns to be found within them. every corner of the universe is this way. that's just the way it is. it's your job to find those patterns. this is a fun job, i'll admit, and can be very rewarding
